<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The biggest bottleneck of plugin loading is due to cases when the file is not found on the given paths; when it is not, an error is pushed onto the PHP error stack -- a very expensive operation that often takes up to 10 times as long as the actual include() call.</p>

<p>A file path cache should be added to Zend_Loader::loadFile() to allow caching the success or failure of loading so that in subsequent requests for the given path/file combination, the method may return early if the combination will not resolve.</p>

    </div>
